    <!-- Mission & Values Section -->
    <section class="section values-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="mission-box">
                <h3>Our Mission</h3>
                <p>We transform complex healthcare challenges into clear, compassionate digital experiences that improve outcomes, build trust, and advance health equity.</p>
            </div>
            
            <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top: 4rem;">Our Values</h2>
            <div class="values-grid">
                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Human-centered healthcare</h3>
                    <p>We design for real people facing real health challenges. Every decision prioritizes the patient experience while supporting clinical workflows and organizational goals.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Clinical integrity</h3>
                    <p>We bring genuine healthcare expertise to every project, understanding clinical workflows, regulatory requirements, and the operational realities of healthcare delivery.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Evidence-based design</h3>
                    <p>Our work is grounded in research, data, and measurable outcomes. We validate assumptions through user testing and track impact through meaningful metrics.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Health equity</h3>
                    <p>Exceptional healthcare experiences should be accessible to everyone. Our designs prioritize accessibility, cultural sensitivity, and inclusive practices.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value-card">
                    <h3>Transparency & partnership</h3>
                    <p>We work as an extension of our clients' teams, sharing knowledge generously and building capabilities within their organizations.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Design Principles Section -->
    <section class="section principles-section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">How we think about healthcare design</h2>
            
            <div class="principles-grid">
                <div class="principle">
                    <h3>Design for the vulnerable moment</h3>
                    <p>Healthcare users are often stressed, scared, or unwell. Our designs provide clarity and calm exactly when it's needed most.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle">
                    <h3>Clarity over cleverness</h3>
                    <p>Health information must be immediately understandable. We choose plain language and clear hierarchy over design trends that sacrifice usability.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle">
                    <h3>Accessibility is not optional</h3>
                    <p>Universal design serves everyone better. We design to WCAG 2.1 AA standards as a baseline, not an afterthought.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle">
                    <h3>Respect privacy and dignity</h3>
                    <p>Healthcare is deeply personal. Every design decision considers the sensitivity of health information and the dignity of patients.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle">
                    <h3>Support clinical expertise</h3>
                    <p>Design should enhance clinical judgment, not hinder it. We respect the provider-patient relationship in everything we create.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="principle">
                    <h3>Design for the care continuum</h3>
                    <p>Healthcare is a journey, not a transaction. Our solutions consider the entire experience from awareness through aftercare.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

